    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-07-05T04:10:04+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-05T04:10:04+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-04T18:40:04Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-04T18:40:04Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A high pressure system centred south of the Bight extends a ridge over SA. The high will move eastwards to be centred near Tasmania later on Sunday and Monday but will continue to extend a ridge over SA. The ridge will weaken mid next week as a trough moves over the west and north of SA then a cold front will move across the south late Friday and early Saturday.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW015" description="Mount Lofty Ranges" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-07-05T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-06T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-04T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-05T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Patchy morning fog in the north. Slight chance of a shower about the southern Fleurieu Peninsula early this morning. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. Light winds becoming easterly 15 to 20 km/h in the morning then becoming light in the late afternoon. Daytime maximum temperatures between 10 and 13.</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection not recommended, UV Index predicted to reach 2 [Low]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-07-06T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-07T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-05T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-06T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog in the north. Light winds becoming easterly 15 to 20 km/h in the middle of the day then becoming light in the late evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 2 and 5 with daytime temperatures reaching between 11 and 14.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-07-07T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-08T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-06T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-07T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog about the southern Fleurieu Peninsula. Winds easterly 15 to 20 km/h becoming light during the afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 4 and 7 with daytime temperatures reaching between 13 and 16.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-07-08T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-09T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-07T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-08T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog near the Barossa Valley. Light winds becoming northeasterly 15 to 20 km/h during the day then becoming light during the afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 3 and 6 with daytime temperatures reaching between 12 and 15.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
